    <section id="idm503714746768">
      <title>Convolution is Distributive: Parallel LTI Systems</title>
      <para id="idm503714745472">Suppose now that one input <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x[n]</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is fed into two different LTI systems, and then the two outputs are then summed to form a new output:
</para>
      <figure id="parsys1"><media id="parsys1-plot" alt="Image">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/parallel.png"/>
        </media>
        
      <caption>A parallel combination of LTI systems.</caption></figure><para id="idm503714739168">
Just as with the cascaded systems, this parallel arrangement of LTI systems can also be expressed as a single system, because of the distributive property of convolution, that <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">x[n]*h_1[n]+x[n]*h_2[n]=x[n] * (h_1[n]+h_2[n])</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>:
</para>
      <figure id="parsys"><media id="parsys-plot" alt="Image">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/parallelequiv.png"/>
        </media>
        
      <caption>A parallel combination of two LTI systems is equivalent to a single system whose impulse response is the sum of the parallel systems' impulse responses.</caption></figure><para id="idm503714713824">
The proof of this property is a consequence of the distributive property of addition:<m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mtable columnalign="right left right left right left right left right left right left" rowspacing="3pt" columnspacing="0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle="true"><m:mtr><m:mtd><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo></m:mtd><m:mtd><m:mi/><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:munderover><m:mo>∑</m:mo><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:munderover><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:munderover><m:mo>∑</m:mo><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:munderover><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo></m:mtd></m:mtr><m:mtr><m:mtd/><m:mtd><m:mi/><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:munderover><m:mo>∑</m:mo><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:munderover><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mtd></m:mtr><m:mtr><m:mtd/><m:mtd><m:mi/><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:munderover><m:mo>∑</m:mo><m:mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mi mathvariant="normal">∞</m:mi></m:munderover><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo></m:mtd></m:mtr><m:mtr><m:mtd/><m:mtd><m:mi/><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>∗</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">[</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">]</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mtd></m:mtr></m:mtable><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">\begin{align*}
x[n]*h_1[n]+x[n]*h_2[n]&amp;=\sum_{m=-\infty}^\infty h_1[n-m]x[m]+\sum_{m=-\infty}^\infty h_2[n-m]x[m]\\
&amp;=\sum_{m=-\infty}^\infty\left(h_1[n-m]x[m]+h_2[n-m]x[m]\right)\\
&amp;=\sum_{m=-\infty}^\infty\left(h_1[n-m]+h_2[n-m]\right)x[m]\\
&amp;= x[n] * (h_1[n]+h_2[n])\\
\end{align*}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para>
